Sentencas: The effect of the cathode-to-anode area ratio on the normalized power density for solid oxide fuel cells was investigated.
Titulo: Influence of electrode configuration on the performance of electrode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A geometrically symmetric cell having a screen printed cathode produced a power density of 0.45 W/cm(2) at 800degreesC. However, using a cathode with a geometric area significantly less than that of the anode can enhance the normalized power density by a factor of two.
Titulo: Influence of electrode configuration on the performance of electrode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, using a current collector with a geometric area less than that of the cathode contributes an additional enhancement that leads to an apparent power density of 1.2 W/cm(2).
Titulo: Influence of electrode configuration on the performance of electrode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This difference in cell performance is interpreted as an artifact of normalization.
Titulo: Influence of electrode configuration on the performance of electrode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: When the performance of the cathode is improved using optimized processing technology and careful control of electrode microstructure, the effect of the area ratio on the normalized power density enhancement is less pronounced.
Titulo: Influence of electrode configuration on the performance of electrode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Only testing in a symmetric cell configuration can result in power densities that are also achievable in stacks.
Titulo: Influence of electrode configuration on the performance of electrode-supported solid oxide fuel cells
